===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[school]] [[night]]}}

# An evening before a [[typical]] [[school]] [[day]]; [[normal]]ly a Sunday, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday or Thursday night.
#: ''Jamie has to go to bed at 9:00 on '''school nights''', but on Friday and Saturday he gets to stay up as late as he wants.''

====Usage notes====
Primarily used to indicate that one cannot stay out late; compare with less exact {{m|en|weeknight}}. Also used by working adults, somewhat jokingly, instead of more applicable {{m|en|worknight}}.

